Safa explained that a breakdown in negotiations between the SABC and Sao Tome resulted in a television blackout for local supporters. BackpagePix/Steve Haag Sports JOHANNESBURG - Safa confirmed that Bafana Bafana's AFCON qualifier against Sao Tome and Principe in Port Elizabeth won't be broadcast on local television. The national broadcaster will not have access to Nelson Mandela Bay Stadium on Monday afternoon. In a brief statement, Safa explained that a breakdown in negotiations between the SABC and Sao Tome resulted in a television blackout for local supporters. However, a streaming link is expected to be released for those able to watch online.